http__www_w3_org_2004_02_skos_core_defin: Algal thallus that is encrusted or impregnated with lime with non-calcified articulae rendering the thallus a segmented nature (macroalgae).
Algal thallus not encrusted or impregnated with lime (macroalgae).
Algal thallus that is encrusted or impregnated with lime lacking non-calcified articulae (macroalgae).
So far it has not been reported in literature whether or not the algal thallus is calcified (macroalgae).
